>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Global user</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>3/9/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#FFFFFF>4:41:32 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Miragul Musings: from his descendant =)</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">There are so many posts here I am having a hard time keeping up, so please forgive me if I repeat something. This is more to collect my thoughts and bring ideas from different threads together then to offer antything particularly groundbreaking. (I'm sure someone has thought of this).<br>
<br>
Miragul is probably like Lord Grimrot, Kane and other NPCs... he has a "hard" incarnation (the one everyone is killing) and (in this case I think) INSANELY hard, restored, full, fleshy (not undead) version. The difference is I think you have to do something specific to get him to spawn. <br>
<br>
That's the head I think you'll need: the living one. <br>
<br>
Now, what do you do to get him to become "restored"?<br>
<br>
Has anyone definitely confirmed that the two books given to the Oracle result in the thing that sounds like pteryadactyl (the vial that holds his soul if memory servers me)? If so great... we have the living part of Miragul, or so it would seem...<br>
<br>
Now, I seriously doubt that giving a KoS mob a goodie is going to do much, but do we know if any ERUDITE Necros have gotten close to him? Or is he 100% KoS to anyone that we have seen approach?<br>
<br>
My guess is that the key may lie within Paineel... Miragul is undoubtedly tied to Paineel.<br>
<br>
Probably unrelated, but the librarian in Paineel mentions he is reading a book on "mana collection devices".... I was tooling around as a lvl2 SK so I didn't relly persue it, but it sounds like what Miragul was trying. But anyway...<br>
<br>
Just trying to keep the discussion alvie. Again, sorry to repeat any ideas that may already be out there, or worse yet offer useless info. Just trying to help.<br>
<br>
Good Luck my Brothers and Sisters!<br>
<br>
